In February 2006, the U.S. Department of Labor (DOL) announced its intention to rigorously
enforce the Labor-Management Reporting and Disclosure Act of 1959 (LMRDA) 29 U.S.C. §§
401 et seq. LMRDA requires any Kaiser Permanente (KP) entity that has one or more
employees to file annual reports disclosing required financial dealings with a union, union
officials, their spouses and minor children. The report form is referred to as the LM-10.
This means that each reportable person, including KP managers, KP labor relations
representatives, sales and marketing representatives and consultants/independent
contractors acting as agents of a KP entity must identify and track all reportable payments to
a union. union official. spouse or minor child of a union official.
The deadline for LM-10 Reporting to the Department of Labor is typically March of the
